  "tweets": [
    {
      "id": "2052010659366224176",
      "text": "It seems to me that an “AI law firm” is just a law firm with lawyers using AI. \n\nSo if most law firms now use AI, wouldn’t they all be “AI law firms”? \n\nSeems like a marketing ploy to me. I like it, but at the end of the day a lawyer is doing the work.",
      "author_id": "2843928804",
      "username": "ordonez_adan",
      "name": "Adan Ordonez",
