      "tweet_url": "https://x.com/ordonez_adan/status/2050862972155871246"
    },
    {
      "id": "2050561022134784368",
      "text": "The AI workflows that actually work long-term are the ones that failed first.\n\nOne example: I built a document workflow for a property management company and didn't account for county-specific formatting. One county came back and said the formatting for one of the files was",
      "author_id": "2843928804",
      "username": "ordonez_adan",
      "name": "Adan Ordonez",
      "created_at": "2026-05-02T13:00:19.000Z",
      "conversation_id": "2050561022134784368",
      "metrics": {
        "likes": 3,
        "retweets": 0,
        "replies": 0,
        "quotes": 0,
        "impressions": 207,
        "bookmarks": 1
      },
      "urls": [],
      "mentions": [],
      "hashtags": [],
      "tweet_url": "https://x.com/ordonez_adan/status/2050561022134784368"
    },
    {
      "id": "2050545491050455402",
      "text": "It's not overlooked because because the tech isn't there yet. Doesn't work well enough to make a meaningful difference in a business and anyone who says it does is trying to sell a 💩 version to make a quick buck.  \n\nI tried to set a voice agent up for ~6 months for a tree https://t.co/AjZkv5e7yK",
      "author_id": "2843928804",
      "username": "ordonez_adan",
      "name": "Adan Ordonez",
      "created_at": "2026-05-02T11:58:37.000Z",
      "conversation_id": "2050545491050455402",
