    },
    {
      "id": "2052178054714216874",
      "text": "Use a contribution-floor rule before offering discounts. If a job sells for $2,000 at 55% gross margin, GP is $1,100. A 15% discount drops price to $1,700 and GP to $800, a 27% GP hit. Require manager approval for any discount over 5% to protect growth cash.",
